This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=5249

Easy toggle between different number modes in vim: nonumber, absolute and relative number, with just one key sequence to rule it all. Most other plugins don&#039t provide a seamless way to do all 3 modes at once.

Cycle through the modes by invoking the key sequence <Leader>n repeatedly.

Source: https://github.com/tkhoa2711/vim-togglenumber

